<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-01-27T23:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-01-27T23:00:00-05:00" n="401" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d401">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.05/251: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Shanghai</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Cunningham</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-01-28T12:00:00+08:00">January 28,
                                1930—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received January 28—1:25
                            a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>The following from Perkins: In view of the Minister’s arrival today I
                            shall be glad to receive soon as possible the Department’s instructions
                            as requested in the Legation’s No. 71 of January 23, 3 p.m.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Cunningham</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>